    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk, it feels like when people bring up \"proliferation\" or \"safety\" in 2024 they're just using outdated talking points to stall. like, if we don't go nuclear, we definitely miss the net zero goals. wouldn't u say that prioritizing the climate crisis makes the other risks almost secondary or at least something we just have to accept to survive?",
