      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Prioritizing the existential threat of climate change naturally elevates the urgency for any low-carbon power source, including nuclear energy. Many environmentalists argue that the certainty of catastrophic climate change outweighs the manageable, albeit serious, risks associated with nuclear technology. This view posits that inaction on climate change presents a far greater, more immediate threat than the risks of a well-regulated nuclear industry. However, this approach requires accepting a high degree of regulatory and technological risk in exchange for rapid emissions reductions.",
